:: Forest Blood Gwylan Rescue
<<effects>>
You hear the trees rustle behind you. You slowly turn to look. Something digs at the back of your mind, as if surprised at the intrusion. It quickly turns to annoyance.
<br><br>

Someone emerges from the treeline. <span class="green">It's Gwylan.</span> <<nnpc_Hes "Gwylan">> wearing a green hooded cloak.
<br><br>

"There you are!
<<if $gwylan.timer.bloodVisit>>
	I got worried after you left the shop earlier."
<<elseif $gwylan.timer.bloodKnock>>
	I heard someone knocking at the shop, and I thought it might have been you."
<<else>>
	I thought I saw you shambling past the shop."
<</if>>
<<nnpc_He "Gwylan">> looks you over, and steps closer. "Oh dear."
<br><br>

You stare at <<nnpc_him "Gwylan">>.
<br><br>

<span class="nextLink"><<link [[...|Forest Wraith Gwylan]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Blood Gwylan Rescue Repeat
<<effects>>
<<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
You hear the trees rustle behind you. You slowly turn to look. Something digs at the back of your mind, as if surprised at the intrusion. It quickly turns to annoyance.
<br><br>

Three green eyes stare from the shadows. A shape like a massive fox darts away, before reappearing somewhere else. It's all around you.
<br><br>

A branch breaks, and your body turns just in time to be tackled by something. <span class="green">It's Gwylan.</span>
<<if npcIsPregnant("Gwylan")>>
	Your body rolls with <<him>>, but throws <<him>> off. <<Hes>> sent reeling, but recovers quickly.
<<else>>
	Your body rolls with <<him>>, before kicking both of your legs into Gwylan's gut. <<Hes>> sent reeling, but recovers quickly.
<</if>>
<br><br>

Your body and Gwylan stare each other down. <<rainWraith>>
<br><br>

"I know you can hear me in there, <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "name">>. I'll do my best, but..." <<His>> voice trembles. "I won't be able to get you out by myself. I need you to fight it, however you can."
<br><br>

<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 4>>
	You feel like a fly trapped between two spiders.
	<br><br>
<</if>>

Gwylan runs towards you!
<br><br>

<span class="nextLink"><<link [[Fight|Wraith Snatched Gwylan Fight]]>><<set $fightstart to 1>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan
<<set $outside to 1>><<set $location to "forest">><<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>>
<<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<set $nextPassage to "Forest Wraith Gwylan 2">>

Gwylan grabs your shoulder, looking into your eyes.
<br><br>

You take in a deep breath.
<br><br>

<<link [[Beg for help|Forest]]>><</link>>
<br>
<span class="nextLink"><<link [[I'm well, Gwylan.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 2]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 2
<<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>>
<<set $nextPassage to "Forest Wraith Gwylan 3">>
Your body speaks.
<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	<span class="green">Your voice cracks.</span>
<</if>>

"I'm well, Gwylan. I must have been sleepwalking. Thank you."
<br><br>

<<He>> tilts <<his>> head, looking closer. "Sleepwalking. <<if $exposed gte 2>>Naked.<</if>> Right." <<He>> takes a step back.
"In that case, why not come by my shop? I have a remedy for sleepwalking<<if $exposed gte 2>>, and some warm clothes<</if>>."
<br><br>

You feel a throb in your head.
<br><br>

<<link [[Yes|Forest]]>><</link>>
<br>
<span class="nextLink"><<link [[No, thank you.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 3]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 3
<<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>>
<<set $nextPassage to "Forest Wraith Gwylan 4">>
<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	<span class="green">You lean towards <<him>>, ever so slightly.</span>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

Your body speaks. "No, thank you. I think I'm going..." You pause. "Home." The word doesn't sound right.
<br><br>

<<He>> frowns. "Alright. Let me walk with you, then. It's a dangerous night." You feel another throb.
<br><br>

<<link [[Please|Forest]]>><</link>>
<br>
<span class="nextLink"><<link [[No, thank you.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 4]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 4
<<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>>
<<set $nextPassage to "Forest">>
<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	<span class="green">You manage to let out a short, strained breath.</span>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

Your body speaks. "No, thank you. I prefer the solitude. It's a beautiful night."
<br><br>

<<He>> sighs. "Okay. Well... come see me tomorrow, then. I'm worried about you." <<He>> turns away, but pauses.
<br><br>

<<He>> walks back over to you, and hugs you tightly. Your body doesn't return it. "Your skin is very cold," <<he>> says. "Don't take long. I don't want you getting sick."
<span class="red"><<He>> turns, and leaves.</span>
<br><br>

<<endevent>><<set $gwylanDoesALittleTrolling to true>>

<span class="nextLink"><<link [[Walk.|Forest]]>><<set $phase2 to 1>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 5
<<effects>><<getTarget>>
<<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
<<unset $nextPassage>>

You shamble through the forest. You know-
<br><br>

"Where are you going?" Your head throbs multiple times in quick succession upon hearing Gwylan's voice. "That isn't towards home. That's towards the lake."
<br><br>

You hear rapid footsteps, and <<he>> grabs you by the shoulders from behind. "I'm afraid I have to insist now. You're coming with me, back to the shop." <<He>> grabs your hand, and tries to pull you along.
<br><br>

You don't budge. You slowly turn to face <<him>>. The intruder in your body feels distant for a moment, as if thinking. It pulls against you, testing your will.
<br><br>

After a moment, <span class="green">you start to walk with <<him>></span>.
<br><br>

<span class="nextLink"><<link [[Follow. For now.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 6]]>><<set $phase2 to 1>><<pass 10>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 6
<<set $outside to 0>><<set $location to "forest_shop">><<effects>><<getTarget>><<set $nextPassage to "Forest Wraith Gwylan 7">>
"I've got a remedy that will make sure you sleep through the whole night. I wouldn't recommend drinking it more than twice a week though, unless you want regular sleep paralysis—"
<br><br>

Your body tunes Gwylan out. It does its best impression of normal walking. You feel strange. Almost as though it's going along with you, rather than you going along with it. <span class="purple">It's biding its time.</span>
<br><br>

You make it back to the forest shop with Gwylan. <<He>> leads you to a small table, before heading through a dark doorway.
<br><br>

Your eyes slowly move around the room, catching on a few of the knick-knacks around. "The gull's nest is empty," your body says. "You are all that remains."
<br><br>

"Sorry, what was that?" Gwylan's head pops out from the doorway. You stare at each other for a moment, saying nothing. <<He>> slowly ducks back into the other room.
<br><br>

You stare straight ahead for several minutes. The intruder's will pokes at yours. "<span class='wraith'>Fortunate, <<pcpetname "Wraith">>. Interference from the witch.</span>" You hear something like a laugh.
<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
	"<span class='wraith'>You will be pulled apart between us. Whom do you think is worse?</span>"
<<else>>
	"<span class='wraith'>Let us see which of us claims the fly from the web.</span>"
<</if>>
<br><br>

Gwylan returns holding a tray with a tea kettle. <<He>> pours hot water into a cup, and holds it in front of you.
"There you go!
<<if $gwylanTea gte 4>>
	Sorry that it isn't your favourite butterfly pea flower tea, but I think you'll enjoy it.
<</if>>
Drink it up." <<He>> pinches you on the cheek. You don't feel it. <<He>> sits on the opposite end of the table.
<br><br>

Your eyes look down at it. A <<wraithEyes>> tinge flashes over your vision, and your body feels sick looking at it.
<br><br>

<<link [[Drink it|Forest Shop]]>><</link>>
<br>
<span class="nextLink"><<link [[Do not.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 7]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 7
<<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>><<set $nextPassage to "Forest Wraith Gwylan 8">>
<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	<span class="green">Your arm twitches.</span>
<</if>>
The teacup sits in front of you, untouched. Your body looks back up to Gwylan.
<br><br>

You stare at each other.
<br><br>

"Something wrong?" <<he>> says.<br>
"I'm not thirsty," your body says.<br>
"Ah, drank too much water?"<br>
Your head throbs.
<br><br>

You sit still.
<br><br>

<<link [[Drink it|Forest Shop]]>><</link>>
<br>
<span class="nextLink"><<link [[Do not.|Forest Wraith Gwylan 8]]>><</link>></span>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 8
<<effects>><<set _notMoving to true>><<getTarget>><<unset $nextPassage>>
<<if $willpowerSuccess>>
	<span class="green">Your arm twitches.</span>
<</if>>
The teacup sits in front of you, untouched. "Go on, dear. It will help." You sit still.
<br><br>

Gwylan leans forward.
<br><br>

"I'll stay up with you then. I don't mind."<br>
Your head throbs again. "Why?"<br>
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
	"Because we're one."
<<else>>
	"Because burdens are meant to be shared."
<</if>>
<br><br>

You let out a strained laugh. "<span class="wraith">To think your black heart is capable of such intimacy. Yours is more dead than mine.</span>"
<br><br>

Gwylan blinks. "Well, that was rude." <<He>> leans forward a little further. "It's just tea, dear. It's not like it will... <i>drown</i> you."
<br><br>

<span class="red">Your body lunges for <<him>> over the table.</span>
<br><br>

<<link [[Resist|Forest Wraith Gwylan 9]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Wraith Gwylan 9
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $control gte $controlmax>>
	<span class="gold">You stop.</span> The pale figure doesn't. It flies out of your body as it lunges for Gwylan.
	<br><br>

	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		<<He>> ducks, narrowly avoiding being raked by its blackened arm
	<<else>>
		<<He>> ducks, narrowly avoiding being grabbed
	<</if>>
	as it soars right past <<him>>. <<He>> rushes to your side, helping you stand as the numbness fades from your body. <<He>> stands protectively between you and it.
	<br><br>

	"This is my home. You have no power here. Begone." The entire shop seems to shudder in response. <span class="purple">Dozens of wooden mannequins stand behind the pale figure, each one making a grab for it.</span>
	<br><br>

	It waves its hand, and wooden limbs are scattered everywhere as a single pale tendril whips across them.
	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		It sneers. "<span class="wraith">Cruel gull. <<pShe>> is mine. If not on this night, then the next. I will wait forever if need be.</span>"
	<<else>>
		It laughs. "<span class="wraith">Clever gull. <<pShe>> is mine. I know you understand. To be alone forever-</span>"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	"You aren't ready for forever," Gwylan says back. "You aren't even ready for right now." <<He>> raises a hand and snaps <<his>> fingers.
	The mannequins stand again, and despite many missing arms, they all approach. Most are knocked away and broken further, but a few find their mark, restraining its limbs. It simply sprouts more, which grab and tear the mannequins apart.
	<br><br>

	It turns back with a smug grin, just in time for a ?gwylanItem to bounce off of its head with a loud thud. Its head is knocked to a tilt. It looks stunned for a moment, as if surprised it was actually hit by that.
	It was just a distraction, though. Gwylan runs towards it, a golden bracelet in hand. <<He>> clasps it around the figure's arm, and yells a command.
	<br><br>

	<b>"<span class="witch">Go home!</span>"</b>
	<br><br>

	A matching golden shackle appears around the bracelet. The nearest window flies open on its own as Gwylan darts back to your side. <span class="purple">A screeching wind rips through the air, towards the window.</span> The figure is yanked towards it.
	Its many hands grip the window frame for purchase, but each one becomes clasped in another golden shackle. It gives you both one last piercing look, before <span class="green">it's expelled from the shop</span>.
<<else>>
	Gwylan ducks, narrowly avoiding your lunge. You land behind <<him>> and turn.
	<br><br>

	"This is my home. You have no power here. Begone." The entire shop seems to shudder in response. <span class="purple">Dozens of wooden hands wrap around your arms and legs. You're surrounded by mannequins.</span>
	<br><br>

	Your body struggles against them.
	<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>
		It sneers. "<span class="wraith">Cruel gull. <<pShe>> is mine. Join us. We can share this bliss forever.</span>"
	<<else>>
		It laughs. "<span class="wraith">Clever gull. <<pShe>> is mine. Join us. We can share this bliss forever.</span>"
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	"You aren't ready for forever," Gwylan says back. "You aren't even ready for right now."
	<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion gte 4>>
		<<He>> slowly, but confidently, walks up to you and places a hand on your head. You don't feel it. "Besides, you're wrong. <<pShes>> mine." <<He>> giggles, before whispering in your ear.
		<br><br>

		<b>"<span class="witch">Sit.</span>"</b>
		<br><br>

		<<hypnosisText "<span class='blue'>Your body sits obediently.</span>">> The mannequins all release you.
		<br><br>

		The Wraith pushes against you, trying to force you to move. <span class="green">It can't.</span> You continue to sit in place.
		"<<pcPetname "Gwylan" "good">>." <<He>> pets your head. You can feel it. The numbness is fading. <<trauma -1>><<ltrauma>><<gcontrol>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> turns your head to face the nearest window, and whispers another command.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> grabs a ?gwylanItem from a nearby shelf, tosses it up and down in <<his>> hand for a moment, and <span class="red">whips it at you</span>.
		<br><br>

		It bounces off of your head with a loud thud, but you don't feel any pain. The intruder feels rattled, though. Just enough for you to exert your will for a precious moment. <<gcontrol>>
		<br><br>

		Gwylan runs up to you, and turns your head to face the nearest window. <<He>> whispers a command into your ear.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<b>"<span class="witch">Go home.</span>"</b>
	<br><br>

	The window flies open on its own. Your vision focuses on something, far into the forest. The trees seem to part for you. It's the lake.
	<span class="purple">A screeching wind rips through the air, towards it.</span> The figure is pulled out of your body.
	Its many hands grip the window frame for purchase, but each one becomes clasped in a golden shackle. It gives you both one last piercing look, before <span class="green">it's expelled from the shop</span>.
<</if>>
<br><br>

The window slams shut. Gwylan holds you tightly.
<br><br>

